      "excerpt": "I recently started adding an AI chatbot to this blog. At first, I thought of it as a small feature. As more posts accumulated, I wanted visitors to quickly understand things like \"what kind of developer is this person,\"…",
      "content": "How My Blog Chatbot Ended Up Using RAG\nI recently started adding an AI chatbot to this blog. At first, I thought of it as a small feature. As more posts accumulated, I wanted visitors to quickly understand things like \"what kind of developer is this person,\" \"what technologies does he mostly use,\" and \"which post should I read first\" without manually digging through every article. Once I started building it, other questions showed up right away. Should I just put the documents into an LLM? Would static search hold up? Did I actually need embedding based RAG? I tried exposing an embedding API through Lightning AI for a while. The chatbot now runs with Modal + PostgreSQL (pgvector). This post is about where that process got stuck, and why the current shape ended up this way. Blog chatbot development stages",
