      "content": "Closing Thoughts\nWhat stayed with me from Leemage was not a flashy technical choice. It was the habit of asking whether a problem would come back in the next project too. Even in side projects, if a problem is likely to repeat, I want to leave behind something reusable. Leemage is probably where that tendency shows up most in my work. It started from cost pressure, but while building it I also had to think about operations, extension points, and reuse.",
