      "excerpt": "That is why lee spec kit is designed to quickly bootstrap the basic documentation skeleton of a project and preserve a feature level flow through spec, plan, task, decision, and PR stages. I cared less about adding many…",
      "content": "So lee-spec-kit Starts by Shaping the Documentation Flow\nThat is why lee spec kit is designed to quickly bootstrap the basic documentation skeleton of a project and preserve a feature level flow through spec, plan, task, decision, and PR stages. I cared less about adding many templates and more about putting context in predictable places, so humans and AI could talk about project state with the same words. What was decided, why it was decided, how far the work has progressed, and what should happen next should all remain visible in the document structure itself. Feature Workflow Pipeline This idea did not appear out of nowhere. I was influenced by the structure of spec kit and OpenSpec. Both projects were compelling because they organize work around specifications and preserve the thinking process before implementation. Seeing those projects made me think this approach would work well with AI collaboration too.",
      "sectionTitle": "So lee-spec-kit Starts by Shaping the Documentation Flow",
