      "content": "Performing Optimistic Updates with React Query\nWe are going to add a like feature to our project. When a user clicks the like button, we will call the API using useMutation. To display the result of the call on the screen, we can invalidate the corresponding query key through the onSuccess callback to refresh the data. However, depending on the network environment, the UI will not change until the server responds. To improve the UX, we can use Optimistic Updates.",
