      "url": "/en/blog/taking-meal-retrospect#role-in-the-team",
      "excerpt": "The team consisted of 2 front end developers, 2 back end developers, and 1 designer, which could be considered ideal, but in reality, I was not much help on the front end (because I knew nothing). Therefore, the other f…",
      "content": "Role in the Team\nThe team consisted of 2 front end developers, 2 back end developers, and 1 designer, which could be considered ideal, but in reality, I was not much help on the front end (because I knew nothing). Therefore, the other front end member took the lead while I followed along. The best part was that I could learn how to progress with the project. It was my first time collaborating with the back end, and I realized that writing documentation, such as API specifications, was quite helpful for collaboration. Initially, the project's goal was concretized into an app, and the lead front end developer suggested developing it with React Native since he knew how to use React. At that time, I didn't know React, and naturally, I didn't know React Native either, so it didn't matter much to me. The lead front end developer took charge of the map and store search features, while I was responsible for the nutrient chart, food search, and addition. Although I didn't fully understand React Native, I could make it work, so I focused on development that prioritized functionality.",
